. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Di-Nizo, C. B. &amp; Ventura, K. &amp; Ferguson-Smith, M. A. &amp; O'Brien, P. C. M. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J." box="[222,446,366,393]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="0117579" refId="ref66405" refString="Di-Nizo, C. B., Ventura, K., Ferguson-Smith, M. A., O'Brien, P. C. M., Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J. (2015) Comparative chromosome painting in six species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia, Sigmodontinae) and the karyotype evolution of the genus. Public Library of Science one, 10 (2), e 0117579. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0117579" type="journal article" year="2015">
Di-Nizo 
<emphasis box="[321,371,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). Variation in fundamental number, with 72 and 76, was reported due to a pericentric inversion affecting one medium and one small autosomal pair (
<bibRefCitation author="Lima, J. F. S. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R. &amp; Kasahara, S." box="[828,1015,403,429]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref68699" refString="Lima, J. F. S., Bonvicino, C. R. &amp; Kasahara, S. (2003) A new karyotype of Oligoryzomys (Sigmodontinae, Rodentia) from central Brazil. Hereditas, 139, 1 - 6. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1601 - 5223.2003.01706. x" type="journal article" year="2003">
Lima 
<emphasis box="[895,943,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Di-Nizo, C. B. &amp; Ventura, K. &amp; Ferguson-Smith, M. A. &amp; O'Brien, P. C. M. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J." box="[1026,1247,402,429]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="0117579" refId="ref66405" refString="Di-Nizo, C. B., Ventura, K., Ferguson-Smith, M. A., O'Brien, P. C. M., Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J. (2015) Comparative chromosome painting in six species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia, Sigmodontinae) and the karyotype evolution of the genus. Public Library of Science one, 10 (2), e 0117579. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0117579" type="journal article" year="2015">
Di-Nizo 
<emphasis box="[1124,1173,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). These variation in fundamental number occurs sympatrically on specimens collected in 
<collectingRegion box="[948,1013,439,465]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Goiás</collectingRegion>
(FN = 72 and FN = 74) and 
<collectingRegion box="[1328,1436,439,465]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
(FN = 74 and FN = 76), states of 
<collectingCountry box="[531,599,475,501]" name="Brazil" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<tableCitation box="[615,702,475,501]" captionStart="TABLE 9" captionStartId="62.[151,239,502,528]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="TABLE 9. Karyotype data of genus Oligoryzomys. Species, diploid (2n) and fundamental (FN) numbers, collection localities, geographic coordinates and reference." pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Table 9</tableCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[715,798,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="59.[151,250,1098,1122]" captionTargetBox="[159,1426,187,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-17@59.[151,1436,181,1073]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 17. Distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens of genus Oligoryzomys. (r) O. mattogrossae; (■) O. microtis; (○) O. moojeni; (☆) O. rupestris; (▲) O. stramineus; (l) O. utiaritensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423661" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423661/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). C-banding metaphases exhibited blocks of constitutive heterochromatin on the pericentromeric region of almost all autosomal pairs. The X chromosome C-band encompasses from the pericentromeric region to the short arm almost entirely heterochromatic. The medium subtelocentric Y chromosome was entirely heterochromatic (
<bibRefCitation author="Andrades-Miranda, J. &amp; Oliveira, L. F. B. &amp; Lima-Rosa, C. A. &amp; Nunes, A. P. &amp; Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S." box="[676,1037,583,609]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1080 - 1091" refId="ref63690" refString="Andrades-Miranda, J., Oliveira, L. F. B., Lima-Rosa, C. A., Nunes, A. P., Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S. (2001 a) Chromosome studies of seven species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia: Sigmodontinae) from Brazil. Journal of Mammalogy, 82, 1080 - 1091. https: // doi. org / 10.1644 / 1545 - 1542 (2001) 082 % 3 C 1080: CSOSSO % 3 E 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2001">
Andrades-Miranda 
<emphasis box="[898,949,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2001a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lima, J. F. S. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R. &amp; Kasahara, S." box="[1049,1244,583,609]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref68699" refString="Lima, J. F. S., Bonvicino, C. R. &amp; Kasahara, S. (2003) A new karyotype of Oligoryzomys (Sigmodontinae, Rodentia) from central Brazil. Hereditas, 139, 1 - 6. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1601 - 5223.2003.01706. x" type="journal article" year="2003">
Lima 
<emphasis box="[1117,1168,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). G-banding was also performed (
<bibRefCitation author="Andrades-Miranda, J. &amp; Oliveira, L. F. B. &amp; Lima-Rosa, C. A. &amp; Nunes, A. P. &amp; Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S." box="[337,696,619,645]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1080 - 1091" refId="ref63690" refString="Andrades-Miranda, J., Oliveira, L. F. B., Lima-Rosa, C. A., Nunes, A. P., Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S. (2001 a) Chromosome studies of seven species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia: Sigmodontinae) from Brazil. Journal of Mammalogy, 82, 1080 - 1091. https: // doi. org / 10.1644 / 1545 - 1542 (2001) 082 % 3 C 1080: CSOSSO % 3 E 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2001">
Andrades-Miranda 
<emphasis box="[559,609,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2001a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lima, J. F. S. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R. &amp; Kasahara, S." box="[709,901,619,645]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref68699" refString="Lima, J. F. S., Bonvicino, C. R. &amp; Kasahara, S. (2003) A new karyotype of Oligoryzomys (Sigmodontinae, Rodentia) from central Brazil. Hereditas, 139, 1 - 6. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1601 - 5223.2003.01706. x" type="journal article" year="2003">
Lima 
<emphasis box="[776,827,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Di-Nizo, C. B. &amp; Ventura, K. &amp; Ferguson-Smith, M. A. &amp; O'Brien, P. C. M. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J." box="[914,1141,618,645]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="0117579" refId="ref66405" refString="Di-Nizo, C. B., Ventura, K., Ferguson-Smith, M. A., O'Brien, P. C. M., Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J. (2015) Comparative chromosome painting in six species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia, Sigmodontinae) and the karyotype evolution of the genus. Public Library of Science one, 10 (2), e 0117579. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0117579" type="journal article" year="2015">
Di-Nizo 
<emphasis box="[1014,1065,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). Multiple NORs, varying from three to ten were localized at the telomeric regions of the short arms on acrocentric pairs from large to small size (
<bibRefCitation author="Andrades-Miranda, J. &amp; Oliveira, L. F. B. &amp; Lima-Rosa, C. A. &amp; Nunes, A. P. &amp; Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S." box="[208,559,691,717]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1080 - 1091" refId="ref63690" refString="Andrades-Miranda, J., Oliveira, L. F. B., Lima-Rosa, C. A., Nunes, A. P., Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S. (2001 a) Chromosome studies of seven species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia: Sigmodontinae) from Brazil. Journal of Mammalogy, 82, 1080 - 1091. https: // doi. org / 10.1644 / 1545 - 1542 (2001) 082 % 3 C 1080: CSOSSO % 3 E 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2001">
Andrades-Miranda 
<emphasis box="[427,475,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2001a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lima, J. F. S. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R. &amp; Kasahara, S." box="[569,755,691,717]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref68699" refString="Lima, J. F. S., Bonvicino, C. R. &amp; Kasahara, S. (2003) A new karyotype of Oligoryzomys (Sigmodontinae, Rodentia) from central Brazil. Hereditas, 139, 1 - 6. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1601 - 5223.2003.01706. x" type="journal article" year="2003">
Lima 
<emphasis box="[634,682,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). FISH with telomeric sequences revealed signals exclusively at the ends of all chromosome arms and no interstitial signals were observed (
<bibRefCitation author="Andrades-Miranda, J. &amp; Oliveira, L. F. B. &amp; Lima-Rosa, C. A. &amp; Nunes, A. P. &amp; Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S." box="[1059,1424,727,753]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1080 - 1091" refId="ref63690" refString="Andrades-Miranda, J., Oliveira, L. F. B., Lima-Rosa, C. A., Nunes, A. P., Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S. (2001 a) Chromosome studies of seven species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia: Sigmodontinae) from Brazil. Journal of Mammalogy, 82, 1080 - 1091. https: // doi. org / 10.1644 / 1545 - 1542 (2001) 082 % 3 C 1080: CSOSSO % 3 E 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2001">
Andrades-Miranda 
<emphasis box="[1283,1335,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2001a
</bibRefCitation>
). Whole chromosome probes of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weksler &amp; Bonvicino" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[493,617,763,789]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Oligoryzomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="moojeni">
<emphasis box="[493,617,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">O. moojeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was made by flow cytometry, from sorted chromosomes of fibroblast cell culture. These probes were used to established maps of chromosomal homology between five 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bangs" authorityYear="1900" box="[1194,1350,799,825]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Oligoryzomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1194,1350,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Oligoryzomys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Massoia" baseAuthorityYear="1973" box="[161,272,835,861]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Oligoryzomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fornesi">
<emphasis box="[161,272,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">O. fornesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[285,409,835,861]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Oligoryzomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microtis">
<emphasis box="[285,409,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">O. microtis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weksler &amp; Bonvicino" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[422,546,835,861]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Oligoryzomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="moojeni">
<emphasis box="[422,546,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">O. moojeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Olfers" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[559,685,835,861]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Oligoryzomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigripes">
<emphasis box="[559,685,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">O. nigripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weksler &amp; Bonvicino" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[737,871,835,861]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Oligoryzomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rupestris">
<emphasis box="[737,871,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">O. rupestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The results showed extensive chromosomal rearrangement, such as pericentric inversions or repositioning of centromeres, Robertsonian rearrangements and tandem fusions/fissions, as well as gain/activation or loss/inactivation of centromeres and telomeric sequences have driven the huge genome reshuffling in these closely related species (
<bibRefCitation author="Di-Nizo, C. B. &amp; Ventura, K. &amp; Ferguson-Smith, M. A. &amp; O'Brien, P. C. M. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J." box="[826,1047,942,969]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="0117579" refId="ref66405" refString="Di-Nizo, C. B., Ventura, K., Ferguson-Smith, M. A., O'Brien, P. C. M., Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J. (2015) Comparative chromosome painting in six species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia, Sigmodontinae) and the karyotype evolution of the genus. Public Library of Science one, 10 (2), e 0117579. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0117579" type="journal article" year="2015">
Di-Nizo 
<emphasis box="[925,973,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). In order to infer the chromosomal rearrangements directions that occurred during the karyotype evolution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bangs" authorityYear="1900" box="[978,1134,979,1005]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Oligoryzomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[978,1134,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Oligoryzomys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the authors compare these results of chromosome painting with a molecular phylogeny of the genus and concluded that chromosomal evolution of these species were associated with both, decrease and increase of diploid number.
